mb|p|nt|Some might open the N hand, but I tend not to open bad 12 point hands. What makes this one bad is the 4333 shape, and the unsupported @CQxx. You can use a program called K&R Hand Evaluator to see what hands are worth ... it is at http://www.jeff-goldsmith.org/cgi-bin/knr.cgi. K&R says this hand is worth 11,50|pg||
mb|1N|nt|You can apply the same standards to the East hand, taking away a point for the 4333 shape, but the East hand also has some positive features, like the 2 Aces and 2 Kings, with the only Jack supported by the AK. KR says this one is worth 15,10, so I'd open 1NT.|pg||
mb|p|nt|By the way ... don't use this during the game ... afterwards, it is useful to see how you did with your hand evaluation.|pg||
mb|p|nt|I would not raise with the West hand. Some 8 point hands are worth more than others. This is particularly bad because 7/8 points are in short suits, and the long suits are weak. KR gives this one 5,25. If you do decide to raise with the West hand, you should use Stayman first to look for a 4-4  spade fit.|pg||
