nt|If opener has a balanced hand, he can bid NT to show a range of points, and then you can use Stayman and Transfers to find the right spot. And if he has an Unbalanced hand, your points will only be useful if they're in pard's long suits. I like to play that 2@D is "Negative or Waiting". If East's diamonds were long and strong, bid 3@d over 2@c.|pg||
