mb|p|mb|4N|nt|West can pass 3NT, but won't with this hand. 4NT is an invitation to slam. You only use Blackwood when you have a fit agreed. Now, that's a pretty losely defined invitation, since East's points are not well defined, but, I'd say this is enough to give it a try.|pg||
