mb|p|mb|6N|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|As the cards lie, you can make 7@C or 7NT but, it depends on a 3-3 club break, which is only about a 35% chance.|pg||
nt|South has a terrible hand to lead from :< Against 6NT, you want to find the safest lead possible. It is nice to have something like J1098 or QJ109. No such luck here, so I'd lead dummy's suit: the clubs are likely to be long and pretty well solid, so the lead won't give anything away.|pg||
